urlLink News : "Iraqis are learning the deadly cost of working for the US By Patrick Cockburn in Mosul  05 February 2004  In the northern city of Mosul, Mustafa al-Sheikh, a businessman turned television producer, has just received a letter warning that he will be killed if he works with the Americans.  Mr Sheikh has been hired by the US military to make a film for local television lauding the Iraqi police in Mosul. He did not plan to tell the police about the death threats. 'They cannot even defend themselves,' he said."